<F P=100> YUGOSLAVIA </F>
<F P=101> Federal </F>
<H3> <TI>   Army Issues Statement on Depot Explosion </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Army Issues Statement on Depot Explosion </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD1406085694 Belgrade TANJUG Domestic Service in 
Serbo-Croatian 0250 GMT 14 Jun 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD1406085694 </F>
<F P=104>  Belgrade TANJUG Domestic Service </F>
<F P=105>  Serbo-Croatian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Belgrade, 14 Jun (TANJUG) -- The situation is under 
control and there is no danger for the population, the 
information service of the Yugoslav Army's General Staff 
reported after a fire broke out which caused an explosion in the 
Lisicji Potok army ammunition depot Monday evening. 
  The statement sent to TANJUG early this morning says: 
``During a storm over Belgrade, at around 2330 last night, 
lightning hit a depot containing explosives for army drills. 
  ``Fire spread to the depot building, setting off the 
explosives. No casualties have been registered so far. 
  ``The situation is under control and there is no danger of 
the explosions spreading. Residential and other buildings and 
the population are not threatened. 
  "Top-ranking officers of the Yugoslav Army's General Staff 
are on the spot, headed by [Chief of the General Staff] General 
Perisic. During the night the scene of the incident was 
inspected by the head of the Belgrade local authorities, Nebojsa 
Covic," the statement issued by the information service of the 
Yugoslav Army's General Staff says. 

</TEXT>

