<F P=100> BOSNIA-HERZEGOVINA </F>
<H3> <TI>   Croatian President Makes `Official' Visit </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Croatian President Makes `Official' Visit </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   AU1406093694 Sarajevo Radio Bosnia-Herzegovina Network in 
Serbo-Croatian 0900 GMT 14 Jun 94 </F>

<F P=103> AU1406093694 </F>
<F P=104>  Sarajevo Radio Bosnia-Herzegovina Network </F>
<F P=105>  Serbo-Croatian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Dr. Franjo Tudjman, president of the Republic of 
Croatia, and his aides have arrived on the first official visit 
to Bosnia-Herzegovina and Sarajevo, as was announced for some 
time. President Tudjman was met and welcomed by Alija 
Izetbegovic, president of the Presidency of Bosnia-Herzegovina, 
Kresimir Zubak and Ejup Ganic, president of vice president of 
the Federation of Bosnia-Herzegovina respectively, 
Bosnia-Herzegovina Prime Minister Haris Silajdzic, Sarajevo 
Mayor Tarif Kupusovic, and other prominent politicians and 
public dignitaries. 
  The official Izetbegovic-Tudjman talks and the talks at the 
level of the delegations of the governments of the Republics of 
Bosnia-Herzegovina and Croatia opened in the building of the 
Presidency of Bosnia-Herzegovina immediately after the festive 
welcome with the highest state honors. After these talks, Dr. 
Franjo Tudjman, president of the Republic of Croatia, will visit 
the Embassy of the Republic of Croatia. 
  Dr. Tudjman's visit to Bosnia-Herzegovina and Sarajevo will 
end early this afternoon with a luncheon that will be hosted in 
honor of the prominent guest from the Republic of Croatia by 
Alija Izetbegovic, president of the Presidency of 
Bosnia-Herzegovina. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

