<F P=100> CROATIA </F>
<H3> <TI>   Tudjman Confers With U.S. Ambassador Galbraith </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Tudjman Confers With U.S. Ambassador Galbraith </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD1006175794 Zagreb Radio Croatia Network in Serbo-Croatian 
1700 GMT 10 Jun 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD1006175794 </F>
<F P=104>  Zagreb Radio Croatia Network </F>
<F P=105>  Serbo-Croatian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Croatian President Franjo Tudjman today received 
U.S. Ambassador Peter Galbraith in the presidential palace. 
Tudjman informed him about the activities of the Croatian 
authorities in implementing the Washington agreement, and about 
his imminent visit to Sarajevo. He particularly stressed that, 
despite certain rumors in the public, the establishing of the 
Croat-Muslim federation is closely linked with the setting up of 
a conferederation with Croatia. Ambassador Galbraith said that 
the U.S. leadership holds the same stances on that issues. 
  They also discussed the improved bilateral relations between 
the two states and specific steps that need to be taken in that 
sphere. They spoke especially about investments by U.S. firms in 
the Croatian economy. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

