<F P=100> BULGARIA </F>
<H3> <TI>   Deputy Alleges `Ethnic Purge' in Kurdzhali </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Deputy Alleges `Ethnic Purge' in Kurdzhali </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   AU1306201594 Sofia Khorizont Radio Network in Bulgarian 1900 
GMT 13 Jun 94 </F>

<F P=103> AU1306201594 </F>
<F P=104>  Sofia Khorizont Radio Network </F>
<F P=105>  Bulgarian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] An ethnic purge is fully under way in the cultural 
and economic fields and in the executive power in the Kurdzhali 
region; this is a deliberate line being followed by the Rights 
and Freedoms Movement [DPS]. Stefan Stefanov, National Assembly 
deputy for the Bulgarian Socialist Party [BSP], made this 
statement this evening at a news conference in Kurdzhali. He 
cited dozens of examples of leading Bulgarian officials being 
replaced by DPS activists lacking the necessary professional 
qualities. According to the BTA report, Stefan Stefanov 
tomorrow will brief the BSP parliamentary group on the 
activities of the DPS in the region and will demand a meeting 
with Interior Minister Viktor Mikhaylov. 

</TEXT>

