<F P=100> BULGARIA </F>
<H3> <TI>   Second Reactor at Kozloduy Plant Restarted </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Second Reactor at Kozloduy Plant Restarted </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   AU1506101994 Sofia Khorizont Radio Network in Bulgarian 0900 
GMT 15 Jun 94 </F>

<F P=103> AU1506101994 </F>
<F P=104>  Sofia Khorizont Radio Network </F>
<F P=105>  Bulgarian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] The 440-megawatt second reactor at the Kozloduy 
Nuclear Plant was restarted and connected to the country's grid. 
It is expected that by the end of the day it will be 
functioning at 50 percent of its capacity. The reactor was 
switched off for three months, during which time it was repaired 
and refueled. Three additional reactors are functioning at a 
total capacity of 1,400 megawatt. The plant's fourth and fifth 
reactors are being repaired. 

</TEXT>

