<F P=100> CROATIA </F>
<H3> <TI>   Delay in Talks Between HDZ, Opposition Viewed </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Delay in Talks Between HDZ, Opposition Viewed </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   AU1406203094 Zagreb VJESNIK in Serbo-Croatian 9 Jun 94 pp 1-3 </F>
<F P=103> AU1406203094 </F>
<F P=104>  Zagreb VJESNIK </F>
<F P=105>  Serbo-Croatian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [Report by Aleksa Crnjakovic: "The Opposition Will Not Give </F>
Up Mesic"] 
  [Text] Zagreb -- "Owing to the need for consultations 
within our parties, we agreed to conclude them by Friday and to 
agree on the continuation of the negotiations then," Jure Radic 
stated briefly on Wednesday, after the meeting between the 
representatives of the HDZ [Croatian Democratic Community] and 
parliamentary opposition parties that lasted for an hour and a 
half. 
  The representatives of the Croatian opposition have briefly 
confirmed Radic's statement and wanted to make no more comments 
about the negotiations. The HDZ representatives in the 
negotiations are: Jure Radic, Mate Granic, Adam Mestrovic, Ivan 
Valent, and Ivic Pasalic. The representatives of the opposition 
in the negotiations are: Savka Dabcevic-Kucar and Slavko 
Mestrovic (Croatian National Party), Drazen Budisa (Croatian 
Social Liberal Party), Stjepan Radic (Croatian Peasants Party), 
Ivica Racan (Party of Democratic Changes), Ivan Jakovcic 
(Istrian Democratic Congress), and Slavko Degoricija (Croatian 
Independent Democrats). 

</TEXT>

