<F P=100> BOSNIA-HERZEGOVINA </F>
<H3> <TI>   Croatian President Tudjman Visits </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Croatian President Tudjman Visits </PHRASE></F></HT>
<H4>    Tudjman Opens Croatian Embassy </H4>

<F P=102> AU1406162094 Sarajevo Radio Bosnia-Herzegovina Network in 
Serbo-Croatian 1300 GMT 14 Jun 94 </F>

<F P=103> AU1406162094 </F>
<F P=104>  Sarajevo Radio Bosnia-Herzegovina Network </F>
<F P=105>  Serbo-Croatian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] At the opening of the Croatian Embassy in Sarajevo, 
Dr. Franjo Tudjman said, among other things, that he was 
convinced that we were at the end of the tragedy that this town 
and the Muslim and Croatian people in Bosnia-Herzegovina and 
Croatia have had to endure. We can be proud of the fact that 
the Croatian people have contributed greatly to the preservation 
of Bosnia-Herzegovina. [Words indistinct], he said, so that we 
can pick the fruit of the permanent unity between 
Bosnia-Herzegovina and Croatia. 
  Today's official opening of the Croatian Embassy in 
Bosnia-Herzegovina is a sign that we are implementing resolutely 
the Washington agreement on the creation of the federation of 
the Bosniaks and the Croats and the confederation with Croatia, 
Dr. Tudjman said. He emphasized that this was a proof that, in 
search of friendship with the Bosniak-Muslim people, a certain 
level has been reached with the realization of the agreement on 
the federation and that the future confederation is paving the 
way to the end of the war, the aggression, and the tragedy of 
Sarajevo and Bosnia-Herzegovina. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

