<F P=106> [Report by Mirza Sadikovic from Bihac] </F>
  [Text] The fierce attacks by the united aggressors 
[Serbian army, western Bosnian leader Fikret Abdic's forces] 
have continued on the free Bihac region. Yesterday afternoon 
[Bosnian Serb leader Radovan] Karadzic's chetniks from their 
stronghold in Veliki Radic fired several howitzer shells at a 
funeral in Jezersko, and then continued shelling the other free 
parts of the Bosanska Krupa municipality. They have been 
shelling Buzim from the territory of the so-called Serbian 
autonomous region of Krajina, and all night and this morning 
they have been shelling the outskirts of Cazin, Krivaja, 
(Pljanici), [words indistinct], (Spahici), (Gornje Srbljane), 
and [word indistinct]. This is obvious proof of their 
collaboration with Abdic's traitorous phalanx, and yet another 
open aggression on Bosnia-Herzegovina, as they skillfully use 
Abdic as a smokescreen for their attacks. 
  The Kladusa rebels and mercenaries have also continued with 
their bestial attacks along the entire front line. Their 
artillery and infantry attacks never ceased throughout the 
night, and have even intensified this morning. 
  Another appeal has been sent to the international 
organizations to try and save the families that are being 
prosecuted in Velika Kladusa. 

</TEXT>

