<F P=100> BOSNIA-HERZEGOVINA </F>
<H3> <TI>   `Fierce Clashes' Continue </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    `Fierce Clashes' Continue </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD1406150494 Belgrade TANJUG Domestic Service in 
Serbo-Croatian 1345 GMT 14 Jun 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD1406150494 </F>
<F P=104>  Belgrade TANJUG Domestic Service </F>
<F P=105>  Serbo-Croatian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Excerpt] Petrovac, 14 Jun (TANJUG) -- Inter-Muslim clashes 
in Cazin Krajina [western Bosnia] have resumed for the fourth 
day running, local Muslim media have reported. Radio Velkaton 
in Velika Kladusa reports that fierce clashes continued 
throughout the night on almost all parts of the front. The 
fiercest attacks by Izetbegovic's 5th Corps were registered in 
the Trzac, Pecigrad, Liskovac, and Todorovo areas. According to 
the same source, both sides suffered a large number of wounded, 
killed, captured, and missing soldiers. 
  Muslim Radio Bihac reports, and Radio Cazin and Muslim radio 
Sarajevo have confirmed, that Fikret Abdic's units launched 
fierce attacks over the past 24 hours, targeting Pecigrad and 
Todorovo with artillery weapons. Muslim Radio Bihac reports 
that Abdic's forces attacked a bus in the Cazin municipality and 
injured a number of passengers. Radio Bihac also reports that a 
large number of people have been injured, killed, or captured. 
[passage omitted] 

</TEXT>

