<F P=100> BOSNIA-HERZEGOVINA </F>
<H3> <TI>   Serbs: Muslims `Violated' Cease-Fire Agreement </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Serbs: Muslims `Violated' Cease-Fire Agreement </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD1406220394 Belgrade TANJUG in English 2022 GMT 14 Jun 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD1406220394 </F>
<F P=104>  Belgrade TANJUG </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Doboj, June 14 (TANJUG) -- Moslem formations on all 
fronts in the wider region of Doboj, northern Bosnia, violated 
the ceasefire agreement by bringing in reinforcements and 
opening strong small arms and artillery fire at Serb (?defence) 
positions and villages, the information service of the First 
Krajina Corps of the Bosnian Serb Army said on Tuesday evening 
[14 June]. 
  The Moslems were especially aggressive on the eastern sector 
of the Teslic front, where they are threatening Serb positions 
by constant artillery barrage and small arms fire. Serb units 
are forced to return equally strong fire in order to protect 
their positions and defend their lives, the statement said. 
  Moslems also stepped up small arms and mortar attacks on the 
Doboj front, especially under cover of the night. After the 
Serb side returned fire, the Moslems stopped attacking. Strong 
movements by the Moslems' motorized vehicles have been 
registered on this front, around Doboj. The Moslems are 
believed to be bringing in reinforcements from Tesanj and 
amassing these troops near Serb defense positions southwest of 
Doboj. 
  Moslems also attacked Serb positions and villages with small 
arms fire on the northeastern slopes of Mt. Ozren in northern 
Bosnia, and on the left bank of the River Spreca. Serb units 
did not return fire. 

</TEXT>

