<F P=106> [Unattributed report: "Serbian Soldiers at Macedonian Point"] </F>
  [Text] At yesterday's session, the members of the Kriva 
Palanka local assembly asked the Interior Ministry to inform 
them about the situation on the northeastern part of the 
Macedonian [The Former Yugoslav Republic of Macedonia -- 
FYROM]-Serb border. The session concentrated on the disturbing 
news that Serbian soldiers had taken over an observation point 
on the tip Sraza, 250 meters inside Macedonian territory. 
  According to the unofficial data tabled at the session, 
10-15 
Serbian soldiers set up tents near the border villages Luka and 
Podrizikonj about a month ago, and took over the most important 
strategic points for observation of the Macedonian territory. 
The [words indistinct] noticed that trenches were being dug 
next to the tents, as well as movements of transport vehicles 
and material. 

