<F P=100> ROMANIA </F>
<H3> <TI>   Opposition Invites Iliescu To Explain Actions </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Opposition Invites Iliescu To Explain Actions </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   AU1406162194 Bucharest Radio Romania Network in Romanian 
1300 GMT 14 Jun 94 </F>

<F P=103> AU1406162194 </F>
<F P=104>  Bucharest Radio Romania Network </F>
<F P=105>  Romanian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Representatives of the parliamentary parties of the 
Democratic Convention of Romania [CDR] and the Democratic Party 
[PD] held a meeting at the Nastase Club this morning. Following 
the meeting they issued a communique which says that the 
signatory parties -- the PNTCD [National Peasant 
Christian-Democratic Party], the PAC [Civic Alliance Party], the 
PSDR [Romanian Socialist Democratic Party], the PER [Romanian 
Ecology Party], the PL-93 [Liberal Party-1993], the UDMR 
[Democratic Union of Hungarians in Romania], and the PD -- 
representing the entire opposition in parliament, after having 
discussed the current political situation, including certain 
statements and actions by Romanian President Ion Iliescu that 
are unworthy of his presidential office and contradict the 
spirit of Constitution, have agreed to invite President Ion 
Iliescu to give the necessary explanations in front of a joint 
session of the chambers of Parliament before the end of the 
current session. 
  The communique also says that, depending on the president's 
answer to the invitation, the signatory parties reserve their 
right to further act according to stipulations of the 
Constitution. The communique also says that the signatory 
parties reached agreement regarding certain joint political 
actions they will carry out over the coming period of time. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

