<F P=100> ROMANIA </F>
<H3> <TI>   Alfa Cartel Protests `Intimidation' </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Alfa Cartel Protests `Intimidation' </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   AU1406200794 Bucharest Radio Romania Network in Romanian 
1700 GMT 14 Jun 94 </F>

<F P=103> AU1406200794 </F>
<F P=104>  Bucharest Radio Romania Network </F>
<F P=105>  Romanian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] On behalf of the organization committee of the Alfa 
Cartel National Trade Union Confederation, this evening we 
received the following communique: 
  On the pretext of the uncertain nature of the dialogue, 
considering that the government team is including fewer people 
than the trade union team, the executive rejects a meeting with 
the trade union members who have been designated by the assembly 
of representatives who are holding a rally in Victoria Square. 
  The representatives of the government want the number of 
trade union members who are included in the team not to exceed 
15 people, while the trade unions wish to participate in the 
dialogue with a team that includes 40 people. 
  A psychological war has started in front of the government 
headquarters. The first demand voiced at Victoria Palace 
[government headquarters] is that the outside yard in front of 
the government building should be cleared, or the government 
will be compelled to resort to shield bearers. We protest such 
methods of intimidation, the more so since the bilateral 
dialogue has not even started yet, the communique we received 
from the organization committee of the Alfa Cartel National 
Trade Union Confederation says. 

</TEXT>

