<F P=100> SLOVAKIA </F>
<H3> <TI>   Talks on European Security Structures </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Talks on European Security Structures </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD1406203694 Bratislava Rozhlasova Stanica Slovensko Network 
in Slovak 1630 GMT 14 Jun 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD1406203694 </F>
<F P=104>  Bratislava Rozhlasova Stanica Slovensko Network 
in Slovak 1630 GMT 14 Jun 94 </F>

<F P=105> Slovak </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Excerpt] General M.J. Wilmink, commander of Allied Land 
Forces in Central Europe, has arrived in Slovakia for a four-day 
visit. He was welcomed at the Bratislava Milan Rastislav 
Stefanik Airport by the Slovak Army's Emil Vestenicky. Our 
collegue Peter Toman reports on General Wilmink's agenda today. 
  [Toman] General Wilmink was welcomed by the Slovak Army's 
Lieutenant General Julius Humaj in Trencin this afternoon. He 
briefed the NATO representatives about the tasks being currently 
fulfilled by the Slovak Army and also on the transformation in 
the Army and its command to structures comparable to those of 
the NATO armies. In the course of their talks, both 
representatives agreed that the conditions stipulated in the 
Partnership for Peace program offer a realistic basis for the 
incorporation of the Slovak Army into the European security 
structures and thereby, into NATO. [passage omitted] 

</TEXT>

