<F P=100> POLAND </F>
<H3> <TI>   Russia's Shumeyko Comments on Relations </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Russia's Shumeyko Comments on Relations </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD1406200494 Warsaw PAP in Polish 1719 GMT 14 Jun 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD1406200494 </F>
<F P=104>  Warsaw PAP </F>
<F P=105>  Polish </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Warsaw, 14 Jun -- Russian Federation Council 
Chairman Vladimir Shumeyko told journalists after his meeting 
today with Senate Speaker Adam Struzik: "We have common views on 
almost all issues." He did not explain what "almost" meant. 
  He also avoided replying to questions on when Russia will 
join the Partnership for Peace and why President Yeltsin decided 
not to participate in festivities marking the 50th anniversary 
of the Warsaw Uprising. He expressed the view that the 
development of Polish-Russian economic relations depends, above 
all, on creating a legislative basis naturally conducive to 
direct cooperation between companies of both countries. 
"Political resolve will then no longer matter," he said. 
  Adam Struzik said the talks focused on general issues and 
also on concrete matters such as a future meeting of 
parliamentarians of the Kaliningrad oblast and Polish border 
regions. 

</TEXT>

