FOR OFFICIAL USE ONLY </F>

<F P=103> AU1306144494 </F>
<F P=104>  Budapest MTI </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Budapest, 13 Jun (MTI) -- President Arpad Goncz, in 
the course of successive meetings with party leaders, today met 
Ivan Peto, chairman of the Alliance of Free Democrats (SZDSZ). 
They discussed the Saturday explosion damaging a Parliament 
door and agreed that although such incidents are worrying, they 
occasionally occur in almost every democratic society. There is 
no nead for general anxiety, Goncz said. 
  Peto outlined the present stage of the SZDSZ's coalition 
talks with the Hungarian Socialist Party, although not in 
detail. Goncz had ealier said he would not get involved in the 
negotiations. Peto saw the talks on joint Socialist-liberal 
rule as encouraging. A good atmosphere ensures effective work, 
he said. "Socialists and Free Democrats feel it is vital to 
improve government-opposition relations in the future," Peto 
said. 

