<H3> <TI>   Spokesman Recalled From Post </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Spokesman Recalled From Post </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD1306143494 Warsaw PAP in English 1344 GMT 13 Jun 94 -- FOR 
OFFICIAL USE ONLY </F>

<F P=103> LD1306143494 </F>
<F P=104>  Warsaw PAP </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Warsaw, June 13 -- Spokesman for the Defence 
Ministry Colonel Wieslaw Rozbicki has been recalled from the 
post, PAP learnt unofficially Monday. The reason behind 
Rozbicki's dismissal was his article published in the Thursday 
issue of "GAZETA WYBORCZA" in which he argued that Poland's 
signing arms reduction agreements was unjustified. 
  He also argued that shifting the military information 
service 
WSI (intelligence and counterintelligence) from the ministry's 
civilian structures and making it subordinate to the General 
Staff may bring positive results as, according to him, for the 
sake of state security it would be better if a civilian minister 
would not have full access to information delivered by the WSI. 
  In response to the article the Presidium of the Sejm Defence 
Committee charged Rozbicki with "incompetence," "disrespect for 
civilian politicians" and "lack of understanding of the 
fundamental principle of full control of the state authorities 
over the armed forces." Defence Minister Piotr Kolodziejczyk 
also distanced himself from the text of the article. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

