<F P=100> ANNEX </F>
<F P=101> Romania </F>
<H3> <TI>   PDSR Rejects PNTCD Impeachment Plan </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    PDSR Rejects PNTCD Impeachment Plan </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   AU1106183094 Bucharest ROMPRES in English 1546 GMT 11 Jun 94 
-- FOR OFFICIAL USE ONLY </F>

<F P=103> AU1106183094 </F>
<F P=104>  Bucharest ROMPRES </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Bucharest ROMPRES, 11/6/1994 -- "The Central 
Executive Bureau of the Social Democracy Party of Romania [PDSR] 
has learned with surprise of the recent statement of the 
leadership of the National Peasant Christian-Democratic Party 
[PNTCD] regarding the decision to trigger in parliament the 
procedure of suspending Mr. Ion Iliescu from his office as 
Romania's president, speculating on an imaginary `attempt' by 
the head of the state upon the independence of the judiciary in 
the matter of nationalized houses," reads a release from the 
ruling PDSR's Central Executive Bureau, signed by PDSR Executive 
President Adrian Nastase. 
  "This has to be associated also with the PNTCD leader 
Corneliu Coposu's stands taken on a possible amendment of the 
Constitution, to the effect of restoring the monarchy in 
Romania," the release reads. "As a matter of fact, it is 
strange to see justice protected by the leaders of a party that 
has so far accused systematically the justice of `obedience to 
the power,' while President Ion Iliescu has never uttered such 
accusations, his only preoccupation being to see to the 
observance of law and human rights, as established by the 
Constitution." 
  "The PDSR assesses that by the above statement the PNTCD is 
trying to accumulate political capital in the context of the 
street events announced for the period ahead, being also an 
attempt of the PNTCD to strengthen its shaken position and 
monopoly in the Democratic Convention of Romania [CDR]." 
  According to the PDSR, "the statement of the PNTCD's 
leadership discredits its own party, the more so as it is a 
parliamentary party with a certain weight in the political life." 
  "Under the circumstances created by the statement of the 
Steering, Coordination, and Control Bureau of the PNTCD and by 
Mr. Corneliu Coposu's statement, the Central Executive Bureau of 
the PDSR expresses its hope that the PNTCD will reconsider its 
own political strategy and its representatives will focus their 
efforts in parliament on the problems under debate, on the major 
issues marking now the country's political life." 

</TEXT>

