<H3> <TI>   Serb Officer on Albania-Kosova Border Tension </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Serb Officer on Albania-Kosova Border Tension </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   AU1006153494 Tirana ATA in English 1022 GMT 10 Jun 94 -- FOR 
OFFICIAL USE ONLY </F>

<F P=103> AU1006153494 </F>
<F P=104>  Tirana ATA </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Tirana, June 10 (ATA) -- The commander of Serb unit 
in Gjakove, Major Slovan Stanisic, in a recent interview with 
the Serbian TV in Prishtina, acknowledged the fact that the 
border between Albania and Kosova is turned into a 
shooting-range for the Serbian forces against the Albanians. He 
said that since 1991 and up to now, the Serbian border guards 
have killed 40 Albanians and have wounded 15 others, reports 
from Prishtina say. 
  Making a detailed analysis of the tense situation created on 
the Albanian border due to the systematic killings of the 
Albanians, the Serbian major implied that the military tension 
will be escalated. He did not mention the responsible persons 
for the tense situation, but he said that only during the last 
five months 30 incidents have occurred on the border between 
Albania and Kosova. 

</TEXT>

