<H3> <TI>   Paper Warns Greeks Against `Hellenization' </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Paper Warns Greeks Against `Hellenization' </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   AU1306133894 Tirana ATA in English 1016 GMT 13 Jun 94 -- FOR 
OFFICIAL USE ONLY </F>

<F P=103> AU1306133894 </F>
<F P=104>  Tirana ATA </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> ["Attempts of Athens and Greek Minority Representatives for </F>
Hellenization of the South of Albania -- According to REPUBLIKA 
Newspaper" -- ATA headline] 
  [Text] Tirana, June 13 (ATA) -- REPUBLIKA newspaper 
published yesterday a letter of the initiating commission for 
creating the Dhkoema Party in Albania, democratic party of the 
Greek minority in Albania. In this letter, the commission has 
requested from the Greek Government to ready the money, radio 
stations and arms for liberation of Vorio Epirus (northern 
Epirus). 
  Referring to the letter, REPUBLIKA writes that "It is a 
witness of the Athens' attempts and representatives of the Greek 
minority in Albania for organizing the Greek forces in Albania 
in a radical form. Those who have signed the letter request 
from Athens a more careful policy and a greater attention toward 
the Hellenization of the south of Albania. They have generous 
suggestions, and requests for technical means, arms, money, 
self-organization, headquarters in Athens, radio station in 
Vorio Epirus etc. They propose Athens that in the centre of its 
propaganda with Albanians should be stressed that Italy and 
other Western states are not friend countries of Albania. 
Intending to create an isolation climate toward Albania, the 
objective is that Albania be dependent on Greece and in order 
that it might be easier for Greece to exercise its policy of 
dictation. 

</TEXT>

