<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Klaus `Surprised' by Resignation </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   AU1006184394 Prague CTK in English 1751 GMT 10 Jun 94 -- FOR 
OFFICIAL USE ONLY </F>

<F P=103> AU1006184394 </F>
<F P=104>  Prague CTK </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Prague June 10 (CTK) -- Premier Vaclav Klaus said 
he was surprised by the resignation of National Property Fund 
(FNM) Chairman Tomas Jezek and the appointment of Deputy 
Privatisation Minister Roman Ceska as his successor, Klaus's 
advisor Vadim Petrov told CTK today. The premier wonders 
whether the change was not overly hasty and whether the new 
chairman will be able to carry out much-needed improvements in 
the activities of the fund. He told Nova Television today that 
he had not been informed beforehand of Jezek's intention, but 
got the news from CTK. 

</TEXT>

