<H3> <TI>   Ambassador to U.S. Resigns, Comments </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Ambassador to U.S. Resigns, Comments </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD1506165894 Budapest Kossuth Radio Network in Hungarian 
1600 GMT 15 Jun 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD1506165894 </F>
<F P=104>  Budapest Kossuth Radio Network </F>
<F P=105>  Hungarian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Pal Tar, Hungary's ambassador to Washington, has 
resigned. He explained his decision by saying that he undertook 
this task at the request of the Antall government three years 
ago, and this period ended with the elections. 
  The foreign minister has accepted his resignation, which 
will 
therefore take effect from 5 July. According to the cabinet 
chief of the foreign minister, a decision of this kind by a 
leading diplomat is not an extraordinary event in a 
well-functioning bourgeois democracy. This can even be 
described as an elegant step. The Ministry of Foreign Affairs is 
not aware of any similar move being considered by other 
diplomats. 

</TEXT>

