<H3> <TI>   Briefs Zhelev on Privatization </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Briefs Zhelev on Privatization </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   AU1506161594 Sofia Khorizont Radio Network in Bulgarian 1300 
GMT 15 Jun 94 </F>

<F P=103> AU1506161594 </F>
<F P=104>  Sofia Khorizont Radio Network </F>
<F P=105>  Bulgarian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] President Zhelev invited ex-Deputy Prime Minister 
Valentin Karabashev, in his capacity as an expert on 
privatization, to give his views on the amendments to the 
Privatization Act that the National Assembly passed. Karabashev 
advised Dr. Zhelev to return the law to the National Assembly 
for further drafting because the approved changes contain a 
number of imperfections. He voiced serious objections 
concerning the chapter on mass privatization. 
  After his meeting with President Zhelev, Valentin Karabashev 
declared that he is optimistic that the existing imperfections 
in the law can be removed when parliament reconsiders it. 

</TEXT>

