<F P=100> CROATIA </F>
<H3> <TI>   SDA, B-H Croat National Council Meet </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    SDA, B-H Croat National Council Meet </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   AU1506165494 Sarajevo Radio Bosnia-Herzegovina Network in 
Serbo-Croatian 1300 GMT 15 Jun 94 </F>

<F P=103> AU1506165494 </F>
<F P=104>  Sarajevo Radio Bosnia-Herzegovina Network </F>
<F P=105>  Serbo-Croatian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Delegations of the Party of Democratic Action [SDA] 
of Croatia and the Croatian National Council of 
Bosnia-Herzegovina headed by their chairmen, Dr. Semso Stankovic 
and Dr.Ivo Komsic, met in Zagreb today. At this meeting, the 
delegations resumed the talks that were begun in Sarajevo on 1 
June with a view to solving the crisis in Bosnia-Herzegovina and 
implementing the Washington and Vienna agreements. A high 
degree of accord was reached on many issues. Regarding 
Bosnia-Herzegovina as a state, both delegations start from the 
stand that Bosnia-Herzegovina is indivisible and sovereign 
within its internationally recognized borders, that its peoples 
are sovereign on the entire territory of the state, and that the 
Federation of Bosnia-Herzegovina is only a road toward a final 
reintegration of all parts of the Republic of Bosnia-Herzegovina 
within its borders. 
  The two delegations do not recognize the results of the 
genocide and will invest maximum effort toward having all 
escaped and displaced people return to their homes. The 
delegations agree that the persons responsible for crimes 
committed in war cannot be entrusted mandates within the 
establishment of the Federation of Bosnia-Herzegovina, 
particularly in the authorities. 
  The delegations also agree that the creation of permanent 
cooperation between Croatian and Bosniak peoples should be 
worked upon with a view to preserving the independence of 
Bosnia-Herzegovina within its internationally recognized borders. 

</TEXT>

