<F P=100> POLAND </F>
<H3> <TI>   Pawlak Says Steel Strike Opens Market to West </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Pawlak Says Steel Strike Opens Market to West </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD1506203094 Warsaw Third Program Radio Network in Polish 
1900 GMT 15 Jun 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD1506203094 </F>
<F P=104>  Warsaw Third Program Radio Network </F>
<F P=105>  Polish </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] At a news conference in Legnica, Prime Minister 
Waldemar Pawlak has assessed the strike situation in the Polish 
steelworking industry. He pointed out its international 
implications. According to the head of the government, Western 
manufacturers of steel have large surpluses of that raw 
material. We are losing at our own volition, the prime minister 
said, because strikes bring our own steelworks to a standstill 
and foreign competitors can enter our markets. 

</TEXT>

