<F P=100> POLAND </F>
<H3> <TI>   Milewski Comments at Seminar </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Milewski Comments at Seminar </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD1506153094 Warsaw PAP in Polish 1238 GMT 15 Jun 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD1506153094 </F>
<F P=104>  Warsaw PAP </F>
<F P=105>  Polish </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Warsaw, 15 June -- The Armed Forces have been a part 
of the state defense policy, but they should preserve their 
apolitical nature, Jerzy Milewski, secretary of state in the 
Ministry of National Defense said today, while summing up the 
proceedings of an international seminar, "Civilian and 
Democratic Control of the Armed Forces," organized in Warsaw at 
Poland's initiative and with cooperation from NATO Headquarters. 
  The seminar was attended by representatives of 38 states of 
the former Warsaw Pact and the North Atlantic Alliance. 
  Milewski emphasized that the most important decisions on 
defense policy should be made by the authorities coming from 
"free and general elections." Civilian control over the Army 
should not be identified with restrictions, but public 
acceptance is necessary for the principles of the defense 
policy, the functioning of the armed forces, and defense 
spending. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

