<H3> <TI>   Sarajevo Radio: Serbs Step Up Attacks on Brcko </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Sarajevo Radio: Serbs Step Up Attacks on Brcko </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   AU1606094794 Sarajevo Radio Bosnia-Herzegovina Network in 
Serbo-Croatian 0800 GMT 16 Jun 94 </F>

<F P=103> AU1606094794 </F>
<F P=104>  Sarajevo Radio Bosnia-Herzegovina Network </F>
<F P=105>  Serbo-Croatian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [Report by Hamiz Deronjic and Nihad Salihovic] </F>
  [Text] The Serbian aggressor stepped up provocative 
attacks on the Brcko front last night. At about 2000 last 
night, in addition to strong small arms fire, the enemy also 
targeted the Vranovaca-Bodariste area with 60 mm mortars. 
During this period, the chetniks were also observed to be 
amassing forces on that part of the front. In addition to 
firing Browings and machine guns from Lipovac, the enemy also 
fired over 20 grenades on the central part of the defense line. 
  At about 0130 this morning, the chetniks again fired on the 
central part of the front with Browings and portable mortars. 
The activities of the enemy's reconnaissance units also 
intensified on the Brcko front overnight, especially around 
Djukici and (?Pekici). Members of the 108th Motorized and the 
108th Infantry Brigades, as well as the support units from the 
2nd Corps, were not involved in any combat last night. 

</TEXT>

