<F P=100> BOSNIA-HERZEGOVINA </F>
<H3> <TI>   Serbian Army Says Muslims Violated Cease-Fire </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Serbian Army Says Muslims Violated Cease-Fire </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD1606001994 Belgrade TANJUG in English 2346 GMT 15 Jun 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD1606001994 </F>
<F P=104>  Belgrade TANJUG </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Vlasenica, June 15 (TANJUG) -- After a comparative 
lull on Tuesday [14 June], Bosnian Moslem forces on Wednesday 
violated the latest ceasefire on the Kladanj front east of 
Sarajevo by shelling Bosnian Serb positions from mortars. The 
local Bosnian Serb army command said that the Moslems fired 21 
shells on the Serb Army positions, and eight shells on civilian 
targets in the villages of Doli and Trnovo in eastern Bosnia. 
The Serb forces did not return fire, and the attacks caused 
damage, but no casualties, the command said. 
  The Bosnian Serb Army is not responding to attacks, adhering 
to the letter and spirit of the latest one-month truce, signed 
in Geneva on June 8 by representatives of the Moslem-Croat 
Federation in Bosnia and the Bosnian Serb Republic. The Serb 
Army further reported Moslem attacks on military and civilian 
targets in the past 24 hours in most sectors of the Doboj front 
in northern Bosnia. 
  On the Teslic front south of Doboj, the Moslems launched a 
strong infantry assault in an effort to break through the Serb 
lines, but were beaten back, the Serb source said. A Moslem 
sabotage and reconnaissance team was neutralised in the 
southeastern sector of the Doboj front, the source said. 

</TEXT>

