<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [Unattributed report: "Serious Macedonian Border Violations"] </F>
  [Text] Elizabeth Baldwin, chief of the UNPROFOR [UN 
Protection Forces] press service, officially confirmed the 
Macedonian [The Former Yugoslav Republic of Macedonia -- FYROM] 
border has been violated on several occasions by Serbian border 
patrols. The newly appointed Yasushi Akashi's representative in 
Macedonia, Hugo Ansen, in his statement for NOVA MAKEDONIJA, 
pointed out the Macedonian Government and UNPROFOR should 
consider such border violations as serious. Indeed, he said, 
there are no dramatic incidents, but these are clearly cases of 
border violations. Serbian troops have entered into a territory 
which we regard to be Macedonian by all means, Ansen said. He 
also confirmed the reports of a Serbian plane having flown over 
Macedonian territory a fortnight ago, intercepting an UNPROFOR 
helicopter. No shots have been fired thus far. Sometimes, 
Serbian soldiers do point their guns at targets on this side of 
the border, but that is all there is to it, Ansen said. 

</TEXT>

