<F P=106> [Unattributed report: "Serbian Enclaves With Territorial </F>
Autonomy"] 
  [Text] At yesterday's news conference of the Democratic 
Party of Serbs in Macedonia [The Former Yugoslav Republic of 
Macedonia -- FYROM], the party President Dragisa Miletic 
expressed suspicion about the regularity of the coming census. 
He pointed out the Interior Ministry has yet not delivered 
citizenship notifications to about 85 percent of the Serbian 
population in Macedonia. Miletic attacked media in Macedonia 
for writing of Macedonia being allegedly endangered by Serbia 
and of putting pressure on Serbs in Macedonia to declare 
themselves Macedonians at the census. According to him, the 
names of some Serbs, especially those living a longer period in 
Macedonia, are being changed. Miletic also spoke of existence 
of Serbian enclaves in Macedonia, which presently have a status 
of national communities, but, if necessary, will turn into 
territorially independent enclaves. 

</TEXT>

