<F P=100> ROMANIA </F>
<H3> <TI>   Union Action Continues After Negotiations </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Union Action Continues After Negotiations </PHRASE></F></HT>
<H4>    Protest Action </H4>

<F P=102> AU1506161494 Bucharest Radio Romania Network in Romanian 
1300 GMT 15 Jun 94 </F>

<F P=103> AU1506161494 </F>
<F P=104>  Bucharest Radio Romania Network </F>
<F P=105>  Romanian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] The protest action initiated by the Alfa Cartel 
Trade Union Confederation, which was joined by the CNSLR-Fratia 
[National Confederation of Free Unions in Romania] and the 
National Trade Union Bloc [BNS], is still continuing in 
Victoriei Square. 
  Being present among the protesters, Mr. Victor Ciorbea, the 
chairman of the CNSLR-Fratia, stated that, quote, further 
efforts are being made to organize a second round of 
negotiations with the government. Until now those efforts have 
failed, so what is left is the meeting scheduled to take place 
tomorrow at 1000 [0700 GMT]. However, we still hope we could 
meet with the government today, unquote. 
  At the same time, rallies and marches have been organized in 
several towns of the country by the teaching staff of schools. 
Also today, in Mures County, all employees of the Mures Wood 
Processing Company have gone on strike. 

</TEXT>

