<F P=100> SLOVAKIA </F>
<H3> <TI>   Nuclear Plant Reconstruction Contract Signed </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Nuclear Plant Reconstruction Contract Signed </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   AU1506130894 Bratislava SME in Slovak 11 Jun 94 p 2 </F>
<F P=103> AU1506130894 </F>
<F P=104>  Bratislava SME </F>
<F P=105>  Slovak </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [Article by "(popi)": "They Have Concluded a Contract To </F>
Reconstruct the V-1 Blocks"] 
  [Text] Bratislava--The tender process for a contract to 
supply the project to gradually reconstruct the Jaslovske 
Bohunice V-1 power plant--that is, its first two blocks with 
their V-230-type reactors--was completed recently at the nuclear 
power plant. 
  Engineer J. Sidor, press secretary of the Slovak Energy 
Enterprise (SEP), has told us that the enterprise has concluded 
a contract in this connection with the German Siemens company. 
In it, it respects the conclusions reached by the recent 
International Atomic Energy Agency (IAEA) mission and also the 
decision made by the Slovak Republic Nuclear Inspection Office 
on the criteria for increasing nuclear safety for these blocks. 
An undertaking by the supplier to ensure that the costs of the 
reconstruction do not exceed 5 billion korunas forms part of the 
contract. The completion deadline is 1997. The reconstruction 
will take place in tandem with the block's operation. The SEP 
official added that, despite the fact that the V-1 should cease 
operating in the year 2000 (under the condition that the first 
and second blocks of the Mochovce nuclear power plant are 
operating reliably), it is worth investing in the reconstruction. 

</TEXT>

