<F P=100> THE FORMER YUGOSLAV REPUBLIC OF MACEDONIA </F>
<H3> <TI>   Minister Details Serbian Border Incidents </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Minister Details Serbian Border Incidents </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   AU1606110394 Skopje MILS-NEWS in English 16 Jun 94 </F>
<F P=103> AU1606110394 </F>
<F P=104>  Skopje MILS-NEWS </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [Unattributed report: "Border Violations Do Occur"] </F>
  [Text] During yesterday's press conference, Interior 
Minister Frckovski was asked on the current situation on the 
northern border. He answered this was primarily a question for 
the Ministry of Defense, but did confirm the number of border 
violations has increased lately. He stated the following facts: 
  -- 24 May, unauthorized crossing of border by 17 Serbian 
soldiers and 2 officers, who entered about 150 meters deep into 
Macedonian [The Former Yugoslav Republic of Macedonia -- FYROM] 
territory and threatened UN Protection Force units; 
  -- 27 May, Macedonian air space violated by a Serbian 
military plane; 
  -- 30 May, unauthorized crossing of border by two solders 
and 
going 200 meters deep into Macedonian territory; 
  -- 1 June, border again crossed by two Yugoslav soldiers, 
and 
  -- 8 June, tent put up and a trench dug near Kriva Palanka, 
on Macedonian territory by [passage indistinct]. 
  The situation is the same even as we speak, Frckovski said, 
and again pointed out the Defense Ministry is more competent to 
say more on this. In the Defense Ministry, however, they said 
Minister Vlado Popovski was out of town and no one else was 
authorized to issue statements on this. The same answer was 
given by Macedonian Army General Staff officials. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

