<H3> <TI>   Romania's Nastase Visits, Meets Officials </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Romania's Nastase Visits, Meets Officials </PHRASE></F></HT>
<H4>    Nastase Hopes For Improved Ties </H4>

<F P=102> AU1406201894 Prague CTK in English 1526 GMT 14 Jun 94 -- FOR 
OFFICIAL USE ONLY </F>

<F P=103> AU1406201894 </F>
<F P=104>  Prague CTK </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Prague, June 14 (CTK) -- Adrian Nastase, speaker of 
the Romanian Parliament, said he would like to see a greater 
exchange of information with the Czech Republic concerning 
legislative experiences in the processes of democratization and 
economic reform. Speaking at a press conference today he 
conceded that Romanian-Czech relations were as yet on a low 
level. However, Romania, with a population of 23 million and 
access to the Black Sea, could in future become a significant 
trade partner for the Czech Republic. 
  Deeper relations can be promoted by Czech President Vaclav 
Havel's forthcoming visit to Bucharest, he said. Havel will be 
accompanied by a delegation which includes Czech Privatization 
Minister Jiri Skalicky. 
  Nastase began a four-day visit to the Czech Republic on June 
12. Nastase said he had not discussed the question of Romanian 
immigrants living here illegally with Czech politicians. He 
said in this area "serious difficulties that have not already 
been resolved by our ministries practically do not exist". "A 
few marginal matters" should not impede tourism between the two 
countries, Nastase said. 

</TEXT>

