<H3> <TI>   `Coalition Deputy Prime Minister' Created </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    `Coalition Deputy Prime Minister' Created </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   AU1406123594 Budapest MTI in English 1203 GMT 14 Jun 94 -- 
FOR OFFICIAL USE ONLY </F>

<F P=103> AU1406123594 </F>
<F P=104>  Budapest MTI </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Budapest, 14 June (MTI) -- The Tuesday [14 June] 
round of the coalition talks ended with success as the Hungarian 
Socialist Party (MSZP) and the Alliance of Free Democrats 
(SZDSZ) ended the first stage of talks and agreed on issues 
related to joint government. The agreement includes the 
creation of the post of coalition deputy prime minister to have 
the smaller partner in the government, the SZDSZ, represented. 
  The agreement sets down that the sides will pass decisions 
by 
mutual agreement. If they do not agree on certain issues, the 
matter will go to a coalition coordination council, whose 
members will be the prime minister, the coalition deputy prime 
minister, the chairmen of the two parties, the two parties' 
parliamentary group leaders, plus one member each delegated by 
the two parties. 

</TEXT>

