<H3> <TI>   Horn Briefs Goncz on Progress of Talks </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Horn Briefs Goncz on Progress of Talks </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   AU1406182794 Budapest MTI in English 1601 GMT 14 Jun 94 -- 
FOR OFFICIAL USE ONLY </F>

<F P=103> AU1406182794 </F>
<F P=104>  Budapest MTI </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Budapest, 14 June (MTI) -- Chairman of the 
Hungarian Socialist Party (MSZP) Gyula Horn briefed Hungarian 
President Arpad Goncz on the progress of coalition talks with 
the Alliance of Free Democrats (SZDSZ). Goncz received Horn as 
part of his ongoing meetings with leaders of parties that won 
seats in the new Hungarian Parliament. 
  Following the meeting, Horn told reporters the president had 
welcomed the briefing. He said both the MSZP and the SZDSZ have 
excellent relations with President Goncz, and they have held 
regular consultations with him in the past. The two politicians 
agreed to strive for direct, protocol-free contacts in the 
future as well, with the intention that the new government will 
continuously inform the president. 
  If the coalition agreement is concluded, the new government 
can be formed by mid-July, Horn said. Horn also said he is 
looking forward to receiving the information on the state of the 
country which Prime Minister Peter Boross is to provide to the 
six parliamentary parties on Wednesday [15 June]. He said he 
expects to receive documents regarding the government's 
international and domestic payments obligations, and ongoing 
privatization transactions. He also expects to be informed 
about the country's actual financial situation, particularly, 
how the ministries managed their finances in the last months. 

</TEXT>

