<H3> <TI>   Brandenburg President Discusses Cooperation </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Brandenburg President Discusses Cooperation </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD1506191794 Warsaw PAP in English 1807 GMT 15 Jun 94 -- FOR 
OFFICIAL USE ONLY </F>

<F P=103> LD1506191794 </F>
<F P=104>  Warsaw PAP </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Poznan, June 15 -- Minister President of the German 
Eastern land Brandenburg Manfred Stolpe told a press conference 
in Poznan on Wednesday that his land is particularly interested 
in cooperation with Poland. "Poland is our third biggest trade 
partner, along with Russia and the Netherlands," he observed. 
  According to Stolpe, the last three years were very good for 
cooperation between Poland and Brandenburg. Now the German land 
wants to increase the import of Polish fruit and vegetables. 
Stolpe also said that the developing suburbs of Berlin will be 
a good market for Polish construction materials for the next 20 
years. Brandeburg also wants to increase imports of Polish 
products of the electronics, metal and electrical industries. 
  Deputy Minister for Foreign Economic Relations Andrzej Byrt, 
also present at the conference, said that Germany is very 
interested in possibilities of building in Poland a network of 
highways and high speed railways leading through the Polish 
territory to Belarus, Lithuania, Ukraine and Russia. 

</TEXT>

